args:
The second round of the hospitality face-off is a
demonstration of traditional skills. When it can't
be settled, Ieyasu suggests they determine a
winner by seeing who can gather more New
Year's gifts from Shishimai in an otherworld
location known as the Kagura Stage.
Hospitality Face-Off\nRound Two: Traditional Skills\nBotan VS Addis
What are you doing in the courtyard?
I thought we would demonstrate some\nHinomotoan skills to everyone.
Those who study the martial arts in\nHinomoto seek not brute strength,\nbut exceptional technique.
And now, we shall provide a little\nentertainment to demonstrate\nthose skills.
Looks like I'm first. Right then...
He just closed his eyes and sheathed his\nsword. Am I supposed to be impressed?
Such incredible focus. I can actually feel\nthe tension in the air...
Huh? What did he just cut?
Nothing changed on the striking post.\nDid he miss?
He cut the post so fast, the pieces\nactually stayed together!
Pretty fascinating, ain't it?\nIt's cut, and yet not.
Yes, we're all super impressed...\nbut now it's MY turn!
Next up, the amazing Botan will\ndemonstrate her naginata skills!
It's beautiful! She's flows from one motion\nto the next, and yet never leaves herself\nopen to a possible attack.
This kid seemed a bit scatterbrained\nbefore, but look at her now!
Oh wow! She just cut through all of\nthe training posts at once!
Moving like that with such a long weapon\nis impressive indeed. She is quite skilled.
No more joking around—this round's mine\nfor sure!
I don't know—that sword thing Addis did\nwas pretty darn impressive.
This is going to be a difficult one.
Well then? Which of the two is our winner\nthis time, {player_name}?
This is tough. They were both impressive.
In that case, we'll have to settle this the\nsimple way!
Can't believe I was thinkin' the same\nthing, yet here we are.
What are you two talking about?
We settle it with a duel.
A duel between naginata and sword!\nWatch closely, {player_name}!
It's gonna be totally obvious which one of\nus is better. Now, let's make this...
Ah! Ieyasu got between the two of them\nand stopped it!
He sidestepped Botan's naginata strike\nand deflected Addis' sword blow at the\nsame time!
That's enough from both of you.\nFor what reason are we even having\nthis hospitality face-off?
Sorry, master. Somethin' about her just\ngets me all riled up.
What's the problem here? Fighting each\nother directly just makes it clear which\none of us is more awesome!
Those who study the martial arts in\nHinomoto seek not brute strength,\nbut exceptional technique.
You can show off your strength in a duel\nall you like, but it will not demonstrate\nthe brilliance of your skills.
That would be a poor way indeed to\ndemonstrate hospitality to those of\na foreign land.
You're so thick-headed sometimes, Ieyasu!\nIt's fine to be strong AND skilled!
How DARE you speak to him like that?!\nI'll cut you down!
Both of you, stop that this instan—
Ugh! If you're gonna start fighting,\nI'm calling this whole thing off!
Whaaaaat?! But it was gonna be so cool!
The whole point of having a face-off\nwas to AVOID a true fight.
Both sides are to blame here; canceling\nthe face-off is the only proper decision.
And bad kids who fight on this great day\ndon't get any gifts!
What if we were to determine the winner\nof this bout by seeing who can gather up\nthe most New Year's gifts?
Whoever steals more gifts from\nShishimai will be declared the victor.
Well, there will be a clear winner and\nloser, at least.
But Master, I thought the gifts\nwere for {player_name}.
Which is why he and his friends will also\nbe joining in.
But aren't we supposed to be judging?
We came up with this plan in the hopes\nyou might have some fun.
Now please, go forth and enjoy yourselves\nwhile gathering up New Year's gifts.
Any you obtain will be yours to keep.
Now hold on a moment! We can't very well\nengage in such shenanigans with a\ndragon; the castle will be ruined!
Which is why I prepared a special venue\nfor the event.
It is called the Kagura Stage, and it is an\notherworld born of Amaterasu.
Which means we can be as rowdy as we\nlike without doing any damage.
But how are we going to GET there?\n...Ooooh! We use theeeeese!
Just so. The gleamshards—or otherworld\nfragments, as you call them—will serve as\npassage to the Kagura Stage.
They will cut a path through space in\norder to guide us there.
Then what are we waiting for? Let's score\nourselves some gifts!
All right. We'll do our best!
Hee hee! I'm not gonna give 'em up\nthat easily!
Addis? Botan? Is this plan acceptable to\nthe two of you as well?
I obey you in all things, master.
Throw whatever you want at me—\nI'm not gonna lose!
Then we're off for the Kagura Stage!
I can't wait to see what it's like!
